<i>Do you see my tears?</i>

519
00:42:53,333 --> 00:42:56,509
<i>Do you hear my voice?</i>

520
00:42:56,723 --> 00:42:59,703
<i>Don't be too late</i>

521
00:42:59,940 --> 00:43:04,894
<i>Come over and hold the crying me</i>

522
00:43:05,062 --> 00:43:07,452
<i>You're the only one</i>

523
00:43:19,935 --> 00:43:22,549
Hey! You spent the night away,
how lonely is your room mate!

524
00:43:22,651 --> 00:43:24,773
Furthermore, it's sauna day.

525
00:43:27,033 --> 00:43:28,720
You're feeling embarrassed, right?

526
00:43:28,991 --> 00:43:31,215
Yes, a little.

527
00:43:31,417 --> 00:43:35,919
Thanks to you, last night I could focus fully
and cleared a milestone smoothly.

528
00:43:36,167 --> 00:43:37,170
What milestone?

529
00:43:37,264 --> 00:43:39,942
Someone with writer's block,
finally finished 3 pages.

530
00:43:40,153 --> 00:43:41,535
Well done!

531
00:43:41,774 --> 00:43:43,049
And you?

532
00:43:43,218 --> 00:43:45,526
Have you crossed the milestone with Sung Ah?

533
00:43:45,620 --> 00:43:46,972
What are you saying?

534
00:43:47,003 --> 00:43:49,204
Oh! Good job!

535
00:43:49,386 --> 00:43:52,673
Who says good job?
We just chatted, that's all.

536
00:43:53,211 --> 00:43:55,271
What did I say?

537
00:44:00,469 --> 00:44:03,226
We decided to start over again.

538
00:44:07,019 --> 00:44:08,568
But,

539
00:44:08,857 --> 00:44:11,974
How did you know I was with her?

540
00:44:13,780 --> 00:44:16,071
Your message was too short.

541
00:44:16,230 --> 00:44:18,373
I'll... be late.

542
00:44:18,511 --> 00:44:20,579
Just three words.

543
00:44:20,799 --> 00:44:23,269
You must have tussled over what to say,

544
00:44:23,424 --> 00:44:27,944
Then finally you chose
the shortest sentence, I'll be late.

545
00:44:31,111 --> 00:44:33,411
Don't bother about me.

546
00:44:34,707 --> 00:44:36,196
And don't feel embarrassed about it.

547
00:44:36,354 --> 00:44:39,233
Have a happy, passionate relationship for once.

548
00:44:41,277 --> 00:44:42,795
Fighting!

549
00:45:06,212 --> 00:45:10,170
Can't you be just a little jealous?

550
00:45:16,450 --> 00:45:19,820
Hey! You ignoring me?

551
00:45:20,638 --> 00:45:21,983
Hey!

552
00:45:33,655 --> 00:45:36,743
[I'll be back after seeing Sung Ah, is this better?]

553
00:45:52,895 --> 00:45:54,514
Give me a moment.

554
00:45:59,155 --> 00:46:00,428
What are you looking at?

555
00:46:00,624 --> 00:46:02,226
How does it feel?

556
00:46:02,369 --> 00:46:04,503
Your book is published and
the response is good too.

557
00:46:04,763 --> 00:46:07,071
I feel great now.

558
00:46:08,685 --> 00:46:12,280
Finally, I found out how to
contact Jung Joo oppa.

559
00:46:12,485 --> 00:46:13,992
What were you expecting from me?

560
00:46:14,016 --> 00:46:16,102
There must be water in my brain.

561
00:46:18,200 --> 00:46:20,510
We didn't even talk about that.

562
00:46:20,711 --> 00:46:22,076
Well, it's true, that day...

563
00:46:22,161 --> 00:46:24,188
You cried so terribly,

564
00:46:24,381 --> 00:46:28,317
I don't know how the time just passed.

565
00:46:29,247 --> 00:46:35,746
After you left, I was like
a zombie for a long period.

566
00:46:36,151 --> 00:46:39,228
Finally, I was fired by the office.

567
00:46:39,451 --> 00:46:41,749
I had wanted to go back to live at Jeju island,

568
00:46:41,912 --> 00:46:45,619
But I just couldn't focus and my father
had to give me a good beating.

569
00:46:46,401 --> 00:46:52,195
After a course of twists and turns,
Nan Hee finally dragged me back to Seoul.

570
00:46:53,759 --> 00:46:56,775
Now I eat well and sleep well,

571
00:46:56,989 --> 00:46:58,877
And I'm happy in my job too.

572
00:46:59,055 --> 00:47:01,317
I gave you such deep hurts,

573
00:47:01,524 --> 00:47:04,573
Yet you're willing to take me back.

574
00:47:05,883 --> 00:47:08,816
I had wanted to push you away,

575
00:47:09,460 --> 00:47:11,656
But I just couldn't do it.

576
00:47:11,842 --> 00:47:14,545
Why don't you ask me about it?

577
00:47:16,444 --> 00:47:19,530
I knew I'd come running back to you crying,

578
00:47:19,789 --> 00:47:22,766
So why did I choose to leave?

579
00:47:23,595 --> 00:47:25,642
Aren't you curious?

580
00:47:25,846 --> 00:47:33,310
Whether I saw your albums or
in news report, it just didn't seem real.

581
00:47:35,244 --> 00:47:41,976
But the moment I walked in here,
I understood all about it.

582
00:47:44,323 --> 00:47:48,213
Sung Ah is very successful person.

583
00:47:49,402 --> 00:47:52,192
A person who was so successful,

584
00:47:52,461 --> 00:47:55,819
Was tied down by me for 4 years.

585
00:47:57,477 --> 00:48:00,423
She did the right thing to leave me.

586
00:48:00,743 --> 00:48:02,600
Sorry.

587
00:48:04,777 --> 00:48:07,151
I'm very sorry.

588
00:48:08,514 --> 00:48:10,551
You don't have to say that anymore.

589
00:48:10,711 --> 00:48:13,908
I'll work hard to make up for it.

590
00:48:14,993 --> 00:48:18,177
Your sad period of hurts,

591
00:48:19,070 --> 00:48:21,790
I'll make it all up to you.

592
00:48:28,171 --> 00:48:30,238
There's not even a little echo in this place.

593
00:48:30,422 --> 00:48:34,211
That's how I can hear the most accurate sound.

594
00:48:35,641 --> 00:48:38,243
How long do you practice per day?

595
00:48:38,913 --> 00:48:40,570
12 hours.

596
00:48:40,956 --> 00:48:42,419
Wow!

597
00:48:47,238 --> 00:48:50,369
It's not the same for you, right?

598
00:49:19,628 --> 00:49:23,399
[2007 Collection of New Writers' Works]

599
00:49:35,380 --> 00:49:39,648
Ms. Hong, Be careful or your butt
will be stuck to the floor!

600
00:49:39,816 --> 00:49:41,369
How could they do that?

601
00:49:41,562 --> 00:49:44,148
Why? What happened?

602
00:49:44,633 --> 00:49:47,549
How could they write it so well?

603
00:49:48,347 --> 00:49:49,371
Crazy!

604
00:49:49,499 --> 00:49:51,135
You're mad over a book you wrote yourself?

605
00:49:51,229 --> 00:49:52,323
I'm really...

606
00:49:52,450 --> 00:49:55,697
Not sure what's all this I've been writing.

607
00:49:55,885 --> 00:49:57,292
What are you saying?

608
00:49:57,411 --> 00:50:00,641
Hey! What happened to you?

609
00:50:01,421 --> 00:50:04,829
It's too embarrassing, too ridiculous!

610
00:50:05,291 --> 00:50:07,807
Hyung Tae!

611
00:50:15,911 --> 00:50:18,520
You write well too.

612
00:50:18,746 --> 00:50:22,091
It's hardly half a month to the deadline
for the submission of articles. What should I do?

613
00:50:22,206 --> 00:50:25,686
I read mine again but my work
is too far off, it's not even close.

614
00:50:25,846 --> 00:50:29,467
What if I fail again, Hyung Tae?

615
00:50:29,674 --> 00:50:30,992
What?

616
00:50:31,362 --> 00:50:33,050
It's your first reading of
this author and you like it?

617
00:50:33,191 --> 00:50:34,673
Yes.

618
00:50:35,080 --> 00:50:38,408
You hardly have enough time yourself so why
do you bother to read other people's work?

619
00:50:41,504 --> 00:50:42,926
Let me read it again.

620
00:50:43,137 --> 00:50:45,681
I really like your works.

621
00:50:46,272 --> 00:50:48,775
What do you like about it?
Which section?

622
00:50:48,944 --> 00:50:50,165
Don't you think it's too plain and boring?

623
00:50:50,293 --> 00:50:54,353
Wait...
Have you eaten?

624
00:50:54,477 --> 00:50:56,279
Yes. How about you?

625
00:50:56,422 --> 00:50:58,136
I've eaten, of course.

626
00:50:58,393 --> 00:51:02,193
Hey, take off that tissue stuck to your face.

627
00:51:04,614 --> 00:51:06,883
You want to become a writer that badly?

628
00:51:07,161 --> 00:51:08,378
You think there's no hope too, right?

629
00:51:08,527 --> 00:51:10,770
It's because the deadline's coming and you're anxious,
that's why you're acting like this.

630
00:51:10,925 --> 00:51:13,808
In my job, I have such moments too.

631
00:51:15,774 --> 00:51:17,687
Oh my, really!

632
00:51:17,851 --> 00:51:19,418
Calm down.

633
00:51:19,630 --> 00:51:20,924
You want some water?

634
00:51:21,174 --> 00:51:23,325
No.

635
00:51:30,128 --> 00:51:32,624
Luckily, you came.

636
00:51:33,278 --> 00:51:36,719
At least I feel a little more settled.

637
00:51:54,689 --> 00:51:56,835
Oh my goodness!

638
00:52:01,075 --> 00:52:02,519
Don't cry anymore.

639
00:52:02,643 --> 00:52:04,598
It's interesting.

640
00:52:04,756 --> 00:52:07,333
- Is it really?
- Yes.

641
00:52:10,410 --> 00:52:14,500
But as you get closer to the end,
it loses the plot.

642
00:52:16,276 --> 00:52:18,712
It's alright. Good!

643
00:52:25,702 --> 00:52:27,011
<i>Your novel's the best.
Don't you worry!</i>

644
00:52:27,260 --> 00:52:31,992
<i>Getting that author named "So Woon" under
the flagship of your company is not a bad idea too.</i>

645
00:52:39,932 --> 00:52:41,274
<i>Thanks!</i>

646
00:52:41,402 --> 00:52:45,090
<i>And congrats for getting back
together with Sung Ah again.</i>

647
00:52:46,227 --> 00:52:48,202
<i>If I have any regrets,</i>

648
00:52:48,459 --> 00:52:53,740
<i>It's that from now on,
your life is a finished product.</i>

649
00:52:53,971 --> 00:52:59,305
<i>I'm afraid in future the things I can do for you
will become pitifully few so I regret that a little.</i>

650
00:53:03,702 --> 00:53:06,770
<i>What do you think?
Not bad, right?</i>

651
00:53:06,916 --> 00:53:09,923
Such an impressive writer,
will he work with us?

652
00:53:10,024 --> 00:53:12,461
I'll go ahead and try.
It's a new writer anyway.

653
00:53:12,645 --> 00:53:14,758
You're not the only one reading this book,

654
00:53:15,174 --> 00:53:17,412
This must have spread out already.

655
00:53:17,674 --> 00:53:18,746
You think it's a good idea, right?

656
00:53:18,963 --> 00:53:19,815
I'll just work on it then.

657
00:53:19,964 --> 00:53:22,414
You'll be embarrassed,

658
00:53:23,046 --> 00:53:25,222
This is not a writer we can house.

659
00:53:25,354 --> 00:53:27,062
It's alright if I get embarrassed.

660
00:53:27,150 --> 00:53:29,904
Boss, you want to publish
this kind of books too, right?

661
00:53:30,167 --> 00:53:32,759
If it works, it's a heap of money.

662
00:53:32,806 --> 00:53:33,946
No.

663
00:53:34,129 --> 00:53:35,266
I'll tell her if she gives us
the opportunity to publish,

664
00:53:35,379 --> 00:53:37,527
it doesn't matter if we have
to wait for some years.

665
00:53:37,789 --> 00:53:38,621
Yes.

666
00:53:38,866 --> 00:53:42,847
She's new, maybe she'll be touched by that.

667
00:53:43,096 --> 00:53:45,045
Why are you so indecisive?

668
00:53:45,212 --> 00:53:50,255
Before the reviewers publish
their thoughts, we have to move fast.

669
00:53:50,370 --> 00:53:53,150
Fine. Let's try!
Do you know the way to contact her?

670
00:53:53,228 --> 00:53:55,395
Of course I do.

671
00:53:55,554 --> 00:53:57,281
But is this a guy or a girl?

672
00:53:57,449 --> 00:53:59,222
I think she's a girl.

673
00:53:59,487 --> 00:54:01,660
It'll be better if he's a male.

674
00:54:04,937 --> 00:54:06,181
<i>- So Woon...
- Hello?</i>

675
00:54:06,270 --> 00:54:10,242
<i>I'm away for now...
I want to become an island.</i>

676
00:54:10,439 --> 00:54:11,580
Why?

677
00:54:17,259 --> 00:54:18,673
Firstly,

678
00:54:18,839 --> 00:54:20,940
I'm shocked because he's a guy,

679
00:54:21,272 --> 00:54:24,875
Then the recording on the auto-answering
machine is too low-class,

680
00:54:25,008 --> 00:54:26,848
I forgot what I wanted to say.

681
00:54:26,956 --> 00:54:29,091
Why? What did he say?

682
00:54:29,291 --> 00:54:31,185
Firstly,

683
00:54:31,363 --> 00:54:33,290
We should believe in the product, right?

684
00:54:33,314 --> 00:54:35,398
Yes, of course.

685
00:54:35,500 --> 00:54:37,905
Then I'll leave a message.

686
00:54:39,727 --> 00:54:40,602
I'm back.

687
00:54:40,788 --> 00:54:41,609
- You're back.
- You're back.

688
00:54:41,821 --> 00:54:43,468
You seem to be in good mood today.

689
00:54:43,622 --> 00:54:45,213
Oh! You bought new shoes!

690
00:54:45,472 --> 00:54:48,300
This? Oh! It's a gift from someone.

691
00:54:48,591 --> 00:54:51,551
So who is it from?
What's the occasion today?

692
00:54:51,748 --> 00:54:53,222
It's just from a friend.

693
00:54:53,343 --> 00:54:57,246
Seeing you have clean shoes, I feel fresh too.

694
00:54:57,329 --> 00:54:59,517
You should have done that long ago.

695
00:54:59,749 --> 00:55:03,138
It seems the response is good for our books,

696
00:55:03,376 --> 00:55:06,534
It's such a treat to be rewarded with a meal.

697
00:55:07,002 --> 00:55:08,388
Yes, hello.

698
00:55:08,591 --> 00:55:11,745
[Sung Ah]

699
00:55:13,675 --> 00:55:15,488
Yes, hello, Mr. Writer.

700
00:55:15,691 --> 00:55:19,122
I'm Hong Nan Hee from Jang Comics.

701
00:55:19,589 --> 00:55:23,526
I hope you'll return my call
when you get this message.

702
00:56:36,374 --> 00:56:39,125
I'm sorry to take you out
from your busy schedule.

703
00:56:39,546 --> 00:56:40,821
No.

704
00:56:40,955 --> 00:56:43,563
We'll keep meeting up from now on.

705
00:56:44,694 --> 00:56:47,840
When you see me, are you uptight?

706
00:56:48,141 --> 00:56:50,930
What needs to be spoken, should be spoken.

707
00:57:09,718 --> 00:57:12,277
Why the sudden silence?

708
00:57:12,680 --> 00:57:14,546
Oh! It's past midnight.

709
00:57:14,756 --> 00:57:17,827
- Sung Ah, happy birthday!
- Hey, why are you saying it first?

710
00:57:18,085 --> 00:57:21,501
Oh, I just can't stand you.
So what if someone else said it first?

711
00:57:21,645 --> 00:57:22,130
- Yes so what?
- I should be the first to say.

712
00:57:22,282 --> 00:57:26,745
- Sung Ah, happy birthday!
- Me too!

713
00:57:26,980 --> 00:57:28,418
Thanks, everyone!

714
00:57:28,737 --> 00:57:30,627
Let's sing the birthday song.

715
00:57:30,902 --> 00:57:33,232
Happy birthday to you,

716
00:57:33,440 --> 00:57:35,226
Happy birthday to you,

717
00:57:35,421 --> 00:57:37,705
Happy birthday dear Sung Ah,

718
00:57:37,908 --> 00:57:40,809
Happy birthday to you!

719
00:57:48,916 --> 00:57:50,915
It's raining.

720
00:57:52,248 --> 00:57:55,791
It's quite heavy. Can we climb tomorrow?

721
00:57:57,976 --> 00:58:00,468
Why won't they go to sleep?

722
00:58:18,475 --> 00:58:21,197
Oh! I'm sorry.

723
00:58:30,937 --> 00:58:35,030
<i>At that time, I was dating Seung Won.</i>

724
00:58:35,799 --> 00:58:39,800
After he died, Hyung Tae was
blaming himself for it,

725
00:58:40,105 --> 00:58:45,846
He said it was he who kept pulling Seung Won
along then the accident happened,

726
00:58:46,390 --> 00:58:49,911
I couldn't bear seeing him like that,

727
00:58:51,671 --> 00:58:54,923
I felt that it was my fault instead.

728
00:58:59,171 --> 00:59:04,072
So I just pretended that nothing
happened and decided to leave.

729
00:59:05,111 --> 00:59:08,722
But from the moment I left, I missed Hyung Tae,

730
00:59:10,131 --> 00:59:13,677
And finally I just had to come back.

731
00:59:17,808 --> 00:59:19,778
Don't explain any of this to me.

732
00:59:19,909 --> 00:59:21,960
I'm...

733
00:59:23,261 --> 00:59:25,408
Starting over again with Hyung Tae.

734
00:59:25,639 --> 00:59:28,626
I won't tell him anything, don't worry.

735
00:59:29,027 --> 00:59:30,753
Please...

736
00:59:31,169 --> 00:59:35,339
From this moment on, I will forget it all.

737
00:59:35,750 --> 00:59:38,512
You please forget it too.

738
00:59:41,644 --> 00:59:43,575
I'm really thick-skinned, right?

739
00:59:43,750 --> 00:59:48,809
Don't mention about that ever again.

740
00:59:50,203 --> 00:59:54,120
Seung Won is not coming back,

741
00:59:54,746 --> 00:59:58,856
Thinking it through, it's no one's fault actually.

742
01:00:00,139 --> 01:00:02,582
Let's not make Hyung Tae upset again.

743
01:00:02,736 --> 01:00:04,599
Nan Hee.

744
01:00:06,064 --> 01:00:09,925
Hyung Tae wouldn't even get angry at me.

745
01:00:12,046 --> 01:00:15,390
I made him hurt so much,

746
01:00:15,766 --> 01:00:18,306
Yet he doesn't ask me about it,

747
01:00:18,536 --> 01:00:21,135
Nor does he get upset.

748
01:00:22,482 --> 01:00:25,722
He just held me real tight.

749
01:00:27,905 --> 01:00:31,014
That's why I feel even more sorry,

750
01:00:32,492 --> 01:00:38,254
So I want to hang onto him even more.

751
01:00:56,241 --> 01:00:59,155
<i>Now it begins to feel a little more real...</i>

752
01:00:59,351 --> 01:01:02,965
<i>He doesn't ask and he's not upset,</i>

753
01:01:03,196 --> 01:01:08,098
<i>His expression when he came home
after accepting her all over again,</i>

754
01:01:08,987 --> 01:01:13,982
<i>The process of Sung Ah's perfume
transferring onto Hyung Tae's body,</i>

755
01:01:14,494 --> 01:01:19,671
<i>All this surfaced in my brain just as if
it appeared right before my very eyes.</i>

756
01:01:27,105 --> 01:01:30,480
- I'm back.
- Oh, you're back.

757
01:01:32,217 --> 01:01:34,534
Who on earth is it?

758
01:01:39,421 --> 01:01:41,559
This is number what?

759
01:01:55,109 --> 01:01:56,949
Nan Hee.

760
01:01:57,556 --> 01:01:58,699
Sit over here.

761
01:01:58,820 --> 01:01:59,877
No.

762
01:02:00,052 --> 01:02:02,349
You two go ahead, I'll just leave.

763
01:02:02,525 --> 01:02:03,819
Why?

764
01:02:04,057 --> 01:02:05,659
Sit here.

765
01:02:12,419 --> 01:02:14,340
One more cup here, please.

766
01:02:21,361 --> 01:02:23,333
Here, cheers!

767
01:02:24,855 --> 01:02:28,709
It's been quite a while since
the three of us last drank like this.

768
01:02:33,182 --> 01:02:35,387
What's this?

769
01:02:39,820 --> 01:02:42,585
Nan Hee, you still draw attention, you know?

770
01:02:42,744 --> 01:02:43,944
I know.

771
01:02:44,165 --> 01:02:49,130
I can't do anything about the 8-year age
difference, but I still look quite good.

772
01:02:49,460 --> 01:02:52,560
You get one every Monday,
Who could it be?

773
01:02:52,774 --> 01:02:57,712
Since it's been 5 weeks, it should be in the realm
of a one-sided crush or a stalker.

774
